WEBVTT

00:01.751 --> 00:02.585
<i>Astral: Previously on</i>
<i>The Other Kingdom.</i>

00:02.669 --> 00:03.628
<i>We're about to open</i>
<i>a veil to talk</i>

00:03.711 --> 00:06.464
<i>to my parents about the</i>
<i>destruction of my home.</i>

00:06.548 --> 00:08.758
The Other World is no
longer safe for you.

00:08.842 --> 00:10.760
I will help you get
to know her.

00:10.844 --> 00:12.512
<i>She put me in the</i>
<i>friend zone.</i>

00:12.595 --> 00:15.473
She remains too young to face
this grave threat to our realm.

00:15.557 --> 00:17.976
<i>The truth about Peter's enough</i>
<i>to send anyone into despair.</i>

00:18.059 --> 00:20.145
Life gets complicated
here.

00:20.228 --> 00:22.647
Others have a need
for the truth.

00:22.731 --> 00:23.231
You like him.

00:23.314 --> 00:25.400
You totally like him.

00:25.483 --> 00:26.609
Yeah right!

00:26.693 --> 00:28.319
We just don't need Hailey
hanging around.

00:28.403 --> 00:30.113
Even when they don't know
they need to hear it.

00:30.196 --> 00:32.615
As technology has progressed,
we've forgotten about

00:32.698 --> 00:34.242
the importance of
nature in our lives.

00:34.325 --> 00:37.120
Sometimes there are
different truths.

00:37.203 --> 00:38.371
Don't you like nature?

00:38.455 --> 00:41.708
This research center is going to
attract environmental scientists

00:41.791 --> 00:43.668
from all over
the world.

00:43.752 --> 00:44.544
It's helping nature.

00:44.627 --> 00:47.589
Is there ever just
one that's right?

00:49.716 --> 00:51.134
How long does it take
for the city council

00:51.217 --> 00:53.470
{\an1}to decide on building
permits?

00:53.553 --> 00:56.097
Maybe they already have
and he's out celebrating.

00:56.181 --> 00:57.098
Celebrating?

00:57.182 --> 00:58.183
What are we celebrating?

00:58.266 --> 00:59.184
{\an1}The destruction
of our world.

00:59.267 --> 01:01.436
Our way of life.

01:01.519 --> 01:02.604
End of Athenia.

01:02.687 --> 01:03.271
Oh yeah.

01:03.354 --> 01:04.647
That.

01:04.730 --> 01:06.149
{\an1}How could you eat
at a time like this?

01:06.232 --> 01:09.360
There is never a bad
time for Tex Mex.

01:09.444 --> 01:11.279
{\an1}You scoop it into your mouth
and the fiesta begins!

01:11.362 --> 01:14.616
Olé!

01:14.699 --> 01:15.450
{\an3}Hey guys.

01:15.533 --> 01:16.284
<i>Dad?</i>

01:16.367 --> 01:18.161
City council turned
down my permit.

01:18.244 --> 01:20.497
<i>Sorry gang, I don't feel</i>
<i>like cooking tonight.</i>

01:20.580 --> 01:21.164
Just order Chinese food.

01:21.247 --> 01:22.123
{\an1}Wan sui!

01:22.207 --> 01:24.292
Gong bao ji ding.

01:24.375 --> 01:25.335
It means, "Hooray!

01:25.418 --> 01:27.128
Kung pao chicken!"

01:27.212 --> 01:28.046
{\an1}What?

01:28.129 --> 01:30.131
{\an1}There's more to me than
just outrageousness.

01:30.757 --> 01:32.425
Alright, save me
some mu shu.

01:34.761 --> 01:35.678
Dad?

01:35.762 --> 01:37.096
Don't mind
if I do.

01:37.180 --> 01:38.807
Nacho appetizer before
a Chinese dinner.

01:38.890 --> 01:41.309
Stomach, you're goin' around
the world in 80 burps.

01:42.393 --> 01:44.187
{\an3}Come on.

01:44.270 --> 01:45.522
Did you hear that?

01:45.605 --> 01:46.856
{\an3}Of course.

01:46.940 --> 01:47.690
Trolls have super hearing.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.192
Also, we were all
in the same room.

01:49.275 --> 01:51.402
Morgan, we did it!

01:51.486 --> 01:53.780
We saved the woods!

01:53.863 --> 01:55.865
{\an1}No more building
in the woods!

01:55.949 --> 01:57.200
{\an1}No more building
in the woods!

01:57.283 --> 01:59.702
{\an1}No more building
in the woods!

01:59.786 --> 02:00.411
<i>Hey guys?</i>

02:00.495 --> 02:02.831
<i>(record scratch)</i>

02:02.914 --> 02:05.375
My dad worked really
hard on that project,

02:05.458 --> 02:07.836
and you guys are happy
that it's cancelled?

02:07.919 --> 02:08.669
That's not cool.

02:08.752 --> 02:11.089
I feel badly for that
young Other.

02:11.172 --> 02:12.090
Who cares?

02:12.173 --> 02:13.591
Our baby just
saved the day.

02:13.675 --> 02:14.259
Whaaatt!

02:14.342 --> 02:17.887
{\an1}Ahem, I feel bad
for him too.

02:17.971 --> 02:19.639
{\an1}Seems like a
nice young man.

02:19.722 --> 02:22.559
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

02:22.642 --> 02:24.602
Is there no end
to your thievery?

02:24.686 --> 02:25.895
We're making
a scrapbook.

02:25.979 --> 02:27.230
Out of plant scraps.

02:27.313 --> 02:28.565
Scrap is a
funny word.

02:28.648 --> 02:31.734
Scrap, scraaap, scrrrrrap.

02:31.818 --> 02:33.194
It's lost all meaning.

02:33.278 --> 02:35.780
Father would be so impressed
with these cuttings--

02:38.449 --> 02:40.702
{\an1}You know, Madame
Versitude,

02:40.785 --> 02:42.704
{\an1}"please" goes a
long way.

02:42.787 --> 02:44.247
Winston Althazar, you
are under arrest

02:44.330 --> 02:45.456
for crimes against
Athenia.

02:45.540 --> 02:48.251
If loving my new home is a
crime, I'm guilty as charged.

02:48.334 --> 02:48.918
(giggling)

02:49.002 --> 02:51.296
You think this
is a game?

02:51.379 --> 02:52.380
It isn't?

02:52.463 --> 02:54.424
Only if you consider your
life a trivial matter.

02:54.507 --> 02:56.467
If it's not one thing,
it's another.

02:56.551 --> 02:58.261
Remove him!!!

02:58.678 --> 02:59.262
{\an3}Wait!

02:59.345 --> 03:00.305
You can't do that.

03:00.388 --> 03:02.307
{\an1}Watch me.

03:02.390 --> 03:04.350
Ahh!

03:04.434 --> 03:05.184
Peas!!!!!

03:05.268 --> 03:05.685
<i>Winston!</i>

03:05.768 --> 03:07.437
I'll wait for you!

03:09.355 --> 03:10.773
Ooooh!

03:10.857 --> 03:12.650
<i>Astral: I'm not</i>
<i>like Other kids.</i>

03:12.734 --> 03:14.652
<i>I guess you could</i>
<i>call me different.</i>

03:14.736 --> 03:16.779
<i>Back home, I'm</i>
<i>a princess.</i>

03:16.863 --> 03:20.241
<i>But here I could be</i>
<i>whoever I want to be.</i>

03:20.325 --> 03:23.578
<i>Go to school, make new friends,</i>
<i>explore your ways,</i>

03:23.661 --> 03:25.663
<i>and have some fun.</i>

03:25.747 --> 03:28.249
<i>Hiding my fairy powers</i>
<i>isn't always easy.</i>

03:28.333 --> 03:31.920
<i>But my friends help me</i>
<i>when things go wrong.</i>

03:32.003 --> 03:33.296
<i>I have to make</i>
<i>a choice soon.</i>

03:33.379 --> 03:36.174
<i>Your world or</i>
<i>my home.</i>

03:36.257 --> 03:37.425
Time is running out.

03:37.508 --> 03:40.219
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

03:43.723 --> 03:45.475
Please, say something.

03:45.558 --> 03:47.268
What's new in the world
of geography?

03:47.352 --> 03:48.311
Have they discovered
any new oceans lately?

03:48.394 --> 03:51.606
{\an1}Oooh, tell us the story of
that time you found

03:51.689 --> 03:52.440
an onion ring
in your fries.

03:52.523 --> 03:53.399
It's a real doozy!

03:53.483 --> 03:56.235
{\an1}You can't give us the silent
treatment forever.

03:56.319 --> 03:56.903
{\an3}Try me.

03:56.986 --> 03:58.655
{\an1}Ha, just did, and
you spoke.

03:58.738 --> 03:59.739
Arghhh, you guys
are so tricky.

03:59.822 --> 04:02.450
We're not happy about your
dad losing his project.

04:02.533 --> 04:04.661
We're happy about the
woods being safe.

04:04.744 --> 04:05.453
{\an1}For you!

04:05.536 --> 04:06.412
It's organic.

04:06.496 --> 04:09.999
{\an1}Because I care enough
to polish the very best.

04:10.083 --> 04:12.001
That research center
means a lot to him.

04:12.085 --> 04:14.963
{\an1}And he can still build it, just
somewhere else, right?

04:15.046 --> 04:16.005
I guess.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.466
{\an1}Just remember: there's nothing
we could have done!

04:18.925 --> 04:21.594
{\an1}Astral, Morgan, how
was City Council?

04:21.678 --> 04:24.597
Uh, it was very
informative.

04:24.681 --> 04:27.016
It was uh,
council-icious?

04:27.100 --> 04:28.726
Since when do you
care about politics?

04:28.810 --> 04:31.020
You thought Veto Power was
the Italian exchange student.

04:31.104 --> 04:33.523
Don't forget to turn in your
essay on municipal government

04:33.606 --> 04:35.316
for extra credit.

04:36.567 --> 04:39.237
You skipped school
to go to City Council

04:39.320 --> 04:41.239
the same day my dad's
building was rejected.

04:41.322 --> 04:42.365
{\an1}There is a perfectly
good explanation

04:42.448 --> 04:45.076
for why we
were there.

04:46.327 --> 04:49.539
{\an1}Uh Astral is running
for mayor.

04:50.081 --> 04:51.416
Are you kidding me?

04:51.499 --> 04:52.417
There are things that
you don't understand.

04:52.500 --> 04:55.420
Yeah, like how you can
wreck my dad's project

04:55.503 --> 04:58.047
and still live
in his house.

04:58.131 --> 04:59.882
You're supposed to
be my best friend.

04:59.966 --> 05:05.471
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

05:09.475 --> 05:12.603
Oh, Hailey, Mr. McGillroy
tells me--

05:12.687 --> 05:15.565
Hailey, I know
you heard me.

05:16.024 --> 05:17.400
Oh, hey Aunt Maddie.

05:17.483 --> 05:18.776
Hold on, vibrating.

05:18.860 --> 05:21.404
Mom, you don't say!

05:21.487 --> 05:22.697
Got it, on the way.

05:22.780 --> 05:24.407
Love to stay and talk, but
mom just told me

05:24.490 --> 05:26.534
she had to rush
Benji to the vet.

05:26.617 --> 05:28.077
<i>Benji's your brother.</i>

05:28.161 --> 05:29.078
I know, right?

05:29.162 --> 05:31.581
It's gonna take two of
us to hold him down.

05:31.664 --> 05:31.998
Byeee.

05:32.081 --> 05:33.541
Hailey Grimm.

05:34.709 --> 05:36.085
{\an3}Phone.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.087
Why do adults only use
your last name

05:38.171 --> 05:40.465
when they're really,
really serious?

05:42.050 --> 05:43.468
Hm, no incoming calls.

05:43.551 --> 05:44.093
Wow.

05:44.177 --> 05:45.053
I knew it.

05:45.136 --> 05:46.262
I'm psychic.

05:46.346 --> 05:51.100
My mom will call, and want to
take my brother to the vet.

05:51.851 --> 05:52.602
Any second now.

05:52.685 --> 05:53.561
It's time to make up
your incomplete

05:53.644 --> 05:55.605
in 9th grade Family
Studies.

05:55.688 --> 05:57.815
Why can't we just move
on with our lives?

05:57.899 --> 05:58.858
Forget that ever happened.

05:58.941 --> 06:00.443
Leave the past
in the past.

06:00.526 --> 06:02.945
Those who forget their past
are doomed to repeat it.

06:03.029 --> 06:07.825
Also, those who forget their
pasta are doomed to reheat it.

06:08.701 --> 06:11.120
Hailey, finish your assignment
by end of day tomorrow,

06:11.204 --> 06:12.663
or you get a
failing grade.

06:12.747 --> 06:13.581
This is your
last chance.

06:13.664 --> 06:14.499
But--

06:14.582 --> 06:16.959
I know you want to
graduate with honors.

06:17.043 --> 06:18.461
But you won't with
an incomplete.

06:18.544 --> 06:19.587
You have nothing
to be afraid of.

06:19.670 --> 06:21.798
You weren't there
when it happened.

06:21.881 --> 06:25.760
End of day or your
incomplete is an F!

06:25.843 --> 06:28.805
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

06:28.888 --> 06:31.015
In the case of Winston
Percival Althazar versus

06:31.099 --> 06:33.810
the Realm of Athenia,
you are charged with:

06:33.893 --> 06:35.978
corrupting a Fairy
with video games.

06:36.062 --> 06:38.439
Even at my lowest, I
still looked adorable.

06:38.523 --> 06:40.525
<i>Re-aligning the perfect</i>
<i>works of nature.</i>

06:40.608 --> 06:42.777
Okay, that one
looks kinda bad.

06:42.860 --> 06:43.486
No, I didn't--

06:43.569 --> 06:44.695
Silence!

06:44.779 --> 06:48.825
And finally, trying to eat
Reggie Van Kleekan, stag beetle.

06:48.908 --> 06:49.659
Winston, you tried
to eat Reggie?

06:49.742 --> 06:52.829
He has a wife and larvae
to take care of!

06:52.912 --> 06:55.832
I can explain, if you let
me just tell you I can--

06:55.915 --> 06:56.624
I've heard enough.

06:56.707 --> 06:57.667
Oberon, these are
serious charges.

06:57.750 --> 06:59.627
We have to treat Winston
like a citizen of Athenia,

06:59.710 --> 07:00.503
under Fairy Law.

07:00.586 --> 07:01.796
<i>Versitude: My queen,</i>
<i>you are correct.</i>

07:01.879 --> 07:05.508
For crimes against the Second
Kingdom, you, Winston Althazar,

07:05.591 --> 07:09.053
are sentenced to the Bogs of
Nevermore where you will spend

07:09.137 --> 07:11.639
the rest of your life digging
tunnels for the trolls.

07:11.722 --> 07:13.182
{\an1}Where are the bogs
of Nevermore?

07:13.266 --> 07:14.559
At the edge
of Athenia.

07:14.642 --> 07:17.562
Wear shorts, it gets really,
really hot there.

07:17.645 --> 07:18.646
<i>Oberon: Wait!</i>

07:18.729 --> 07:22.191
If he is to be treated as
a citizen of Athenia,

07:22.275 --> 07:24.694
he will be allowed
to stand trial.

07:24.777 --> 07:25.653
{\an3}<i>Oooh!</i>

07:25.736 --> 07:26.821
This'll be so fun.

07:26.904 --> 07:28.823
I've never been
on trial before!

07:29.282 --> 07:31.576
Sorry Winston,
I'll rein it in.

07:33.744 --> 07:34.787
<i>(knocking)</i>

07:37.498 --> 07:40.209
Well if it isn't little
miss exploding cake.

07:40.293 --> 07:41.711
<i>Come back to</i>
<i>finish the job?</i>

07:41.794 --> 07:43.713
I still have some
hair in my ears.

07:43.796 --> 07:46.757
<i>Take a spot next to</i>
<i>Brendoni over there.</i>

07:47.925 --> 07:50.052
Brendoni, keep a careful
watch on that one.

07:50.136 --> 07:51.554
Trouble seems
to follow her.

07:51.637 --> 07:52.471
Follow me?

07:52.555 --> 07:54.849
This guy's a disaster
waiting to happen!

07:54.932 --> 07:56.184
I don't wait
for anything.

07:56.267 --> 07:58.561
I'm a disaster
in progress.

08:00.146 --> 08:02.148
I don't know how
to respond to that.

08:02.607 --> 08:04.734
{\an1}Alright, everyone, let's
learn some cooking.

08:04.817 --> 08:07.612
You can only survive on mac
&amp; cheese for so long.

08:08.696 --> 08:09.697
Stand back.

08:09.780 --> 08:12.867
I don't want you to be
blinded by my brilliance.

08:12.950 --> 08:14.744
{\an1}I think my retinas
are safe.

08:16.329 --> 08:16.704
Bam!!!

08:16.787 --> 08:20.124
I'm so ova you.

08:20.208 --> 08:21.083
{\an3}Get it?

08:21.167 --> 08:23.628
'Cause "ova" is the
Latin plural for egg.

08:24.670 --> 08:25.713
I could do
this all day.

08:25.796 --> 08:32.178
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

08:32.678 --> 08:33.596
I have to tell
him the truth.

08:33.679 --> 08:35.640
That you're a Fairy!?

08:35.722 --> 08:37.265
{\an1}No way Devon can
handle that.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.268
He gets stressed out
if someone asks him

08:39.352 --> 08:40.770
if he wants fries
with that.

08:40.852 --> 08:41.604
He thinks we
hurt his dad.

08:41.687 --> 08:42.813
{\an1}We did.

08:42.897 --> 08:46.859
If I tell him why we did it,
then he'll see we were right.

08:46.943 --> 08:47.693
No he won't.

08:47.777 --> 08:48.819
Of course he will.

08:48.903 --> 08:49.820
It's the truth.

08:49.904 --> 08:51.739
You're asking Devon to
accept that the person

08:51.822 --> 08:54.784
who's always been there for him
is doing something wrong.

08:54.867 --> 08:55.952
{\an3}He is!

08:56.035 --> 08:57.078
That's what we see.

08:57.161 --> 08:58.746
{\an1}All Devon sees is that
his dad is hurt.

08:59.997 --> 09:01.165
How do I
change that?

09:01.249 --> 09:04.794
{\an1}For starters: don't
tell him you're a fairy.

09:07.588 --> 09:15.221
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

09:15.304 --> 09:16.013
{\an3}Good news!

09:16.097 --> 09:17.014
They're letting me go?

09:17.098 --> 09:17.640
Nope.

09:17.723 --> 09:18.557
Better.

09:18.641 --> 09:20.685
I'm going to be your
defense attorney!

09:20.768 --> 09:21.852
Oh.

09:21.936 --> 09:24.146
Have you ever
practiced law?

09:24.230 --> 09:24.981
Uh yes!

09:25.064 --> 09:26.774
For like the last
fifteen minutes.

09:26.857 --> 09:29.110
<i>You wanna hear?</i>

09:29.193 --> 09:29.652
Laaaaw.

09:29.735 --> 09:31.654
{\an3}Law.

09:31.737 --> 09:33.781
Laaaaawwwwww.

09:34.615 --> 09:39.161
Oh, I'm going to the
Bogs of Nevermore.

09:39.245 --> 09:40.162
<i>Brendoni: Knock knock!</i>

09:40.246 --> 09:42.290
It's troll o'clock.

09:45.251 --> 09:51.048
(singing)

09:51.132 --> 09:51.924
{\an3}Yo.

09:52.008 --> 09:54.677
Your work space is
like outer space.

09:54.760 --> 09:55.553
{\an3}Vast.

09:55.636 --> 09:56.679
And unexplored.

09:56.762 --> 09:59.348
Oh, you think you're so awesome,
with your spanokopita,

09:59.432 --> 10:00.850
and your samosas,
and your cupcakes

10:00.933 --> 10:04.186
and your three-tiered cake,
and your chocolate soufflé.

10:04.270 --> 10:05.354
{\an1}Good golly, you're
an artist.

10:05.438 --> 10:08.774
I can be very productive when
I get to eat what I study.

10:08.858 --> 10:10.693
Which is what got me kicked
out of biology lab.

10:10.776 --> 10:12.778
What do you have to
show for yourself?

10:14.447 --> 10:15.698
{\an1}Ummm--

10:15.781 --> 10:17.908
Less um, more yum!

10:17.992 --> 10:20.369
'Scuse me while I collect
my A-plus-plus.

10:20.453 --> 10:23.331
(baby talk)

10:23.414 --> 10:23.873
<i>Looking good Brendoni.</i>

10:23.956 --> 10:24.874
I mean chef Brendoni.

10:24.957 --> 10:28.836
{\an1}I will not let one class get
in the way of my plans

10:28.919 --> 10:30.963
to graduate as
Valedictorian.

10:31.797 --> 10:33.049
Well, Ms. Grimm.

10:33.132 --> 10:34.759
All ready for
your big test?

10:34.842 --> 10:37.636
{\an1}I Hope you've learned a
few things from Brendoni.

10:42.308 --> 10:43.726
I can do this!

10:43.809 --> 10:46.020
I'm a winner!

10:46.103 --> 10:47.730
It's just me and
a tub of flour.

10:47.813 --> 10:49.649
Nothing to it.

10:54.820 --> 10:56.947
(screaming)

10:57.031 --> 10:58.783
You have to
listen to me!

10:58.866 --> 11:00.743
I had to stop the
research center.

11:00.826 --> 11:01.619
{\an3}Why?

11:01.702 --> 11:02.244
Because you're suddenly
some expert on

11:02.328 --> 11:03.329
what's right for
the world?

11:03.412 --> 11:05.748
{\an1}Come on Astral, you're just
an exchange student

11:05.831 --> 11:06.749
without an accent.

11:06.832 --> 11:07.875
I'm sorry, Devon, but
your dad doesn't want

11:07.958 --> 11:10.086
to see everything
that will happen.

11:10.169 --> 11:13.255
An entire world would have
to move as a result.

11:13.339 --> 11:14.215
And It would
be dangerous.

11:14.298 --> 11:16.759
How about you hop on
the first plane home,

11:16.842 --> 11:19.178
and we can forget
we ever met.

11:19.261 --> 11:20.930
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

11:21.013 --> 11:23.307
I don't need a plane
ticket to fly home.

11:24.809 --> 11:25.893
What?

11:25.976 --> 11:30.064
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

11:30.147 --> 11:31.899
I am fairy.

11:31.982 --> 11:37.029
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

11:42.201 --> 11:44.412
How are you even
doing that?

11:45.871 --> 11:47.289
You showed him?

11:47.373 --> 11:48.457
You knew about this?!

11:48.541 --> 11:49.417
{\an1}No!

11:49.500 --> 11:50.209
{\an1}Yes.

11:50.292 --> 11:51.961
But Devon, you can't
tell anyone.

11:52.044 --> 11:52.878
{\an3}Why not?

11:52.962 --> 11:55.339
{\an1}Do you want to see Astral
on Fairy Autopsy?

11:55.423 --> 11:57.800
Fairies are way more
popular than aliens.

11:57.883 --> 12:00.928
<i>People will take her away,</i>
<i>cut her up, look inside,</i>

12:01.011 --> 12:03.431
and try to figure out what
makes her so different.

12:03.514 --> 12:05.141
They'll think she's
a freak of nature.

12:05.224 --> 12:08.436
Hey, If you guys are in here, it
means you're late for Geography.

12:08.519 --> 12:18.863
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

12:18.946 --> 12:20.364
You look like a
dog's breakfast.

12:20.448 --> 12:21.907
And I should know, 'cause
yesterday I had breakfast

12:21.991 --> 12:23.909
with a bunch
of dogs.

12:23.993 --> 12:25.161
{\an1}Is it hot
in here?

12:25.244 --> 12:26.078
Am I sweating?

12:26.162 --> 12:28.164
{\an1}Are the lights really bright
all of a sudden?

12:28.247 --> 12:28.539
{\an1}Oh no.

12:28.622 --> 12:29.790
(screaming)

12:29.874 --> 12:32.877
Is this what being
a loser feels like?

12:32.960 --> 12:35.504
{\an1}You're really weird and gross
right now, and, honestly,

12:35.588 --> 12:37.506
you've never looked better.

12:37.590 --> 12:39.258
But you don't
seem to like it.

12:39.341 --> 12:40.259
Let me help you.

12:40.342 --> 12:41.510
You can't help me.

12:41.594 --> 12:42.553
No one can.

12:42.636 --> 12:45.389
{\an1}This is not the Hailey I've
come to know and loathe.

12:45.473 --> 12:46.891
Oh, I was like
you once.

12:46.974 --> 12:50.144
I had Family Studies
tied in a bow.

12:51.061 --> 12:52.229
Until--

12:53.105 --> 12:55.524
--the last assignment
of the year.

12:59.445 --> 12:59.987
Here you go.

13:00.070 --> 13:01.906
Chocolate Vinegar Cake?

13:01.989 --> 13:05.868
More like Chocolate
Winner-gar cake.

13:05.951 --> 13:07.620
Okay, that one
needed work.

13:11.290 --> 13:15.211
Just give me the
A-plus now.

13:15.294 --> 13:17.880
In the explosion, my mixer
flew across the room,

13:17.963 --> 13:20.925
which set off a chain
reaction that lead to--

13:28.974 --> 13:32.811
Fire!!!

13:32.895 --> 13:36.148
All because of me.

13:36.649 --> 13:39.527
{\an1}You talk about this explosion
like it's a bad thing.

13:39.610 --> 13:40.569
Get in there!

13:40.653 --> 13:41.403
{\an9}I can't.

13:41.487 --> 13:42.363
{\an1}Can't?

13:42.446 --> 13:43.656
{\an1}That's not in your
vocabulary.

13:43.739 --> 13:44.114
It is.

13:44.198 --> 13:44.573
Can't.

13:44.657 --> 13:45.241
I just said it.

13:45.324 --> 13:46.909
A contraction of
can and not.

13:46.992 --> 13:48.077
Can't.

13:48.160 --> 13:50.246
The Hailey I know laughs in
the face of chocolate cake.

13:50.329 --> 13:52.414
Ha ha ha.

13:52.665 --> 13:53.249
She does?

13:53.332 --> 13:54.416
Yes!

13:54.500 --> 13:58.128
Now are you gonna crawl in a
hole or swing from a tree?

13:58.212 --> 14:01.799
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

14:01.882 --> 14:04.802
Did you not try to
eat this bug?

14:04.885 --> 14:08.931
I-I-I-But Brendoni
said if I eat that--

14:09.014 --> 14:09.640
Arghh!!!

14:09.723 --> 14:10.099
That's him.

14:10.182 --> 14:10.933
Take him away!

14:11.016 --> 14:12.726
I'm sorry, Reginald,
I do not wish

14:12.810 --> 14:15.271
to traumatize you
any further.

14:15.354 --> 14:18.649
The only way we can assure our
fellow Athenians are secure

14:18.732 --> 14:21.151
is to send this Other to
the Bogs of Nevermore

14:21.235 --> 14:23.279
to toil for
the trolls.

14:28.033 --> 14:30.119
The defence may speak.

14:30.202 --> 14:31.537
I've got this.

14:32.288 --> 14:33.664
♪ Lawwwww. ♪

14:33.747 --> 14:36.667
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

14:36.750 --> 14:38.961
<i>Devon: How come you never</i>
<i>told me about this?</i>

14:39.044 --> 14:40.921
We're supposed to
be best friends.

14:41.005 --> 14:42.923
I promised Astral.

14:43.215 --> 14:43.924
What about Brendoni?

14:44.008 --> 14:45.551
Does he know too?

14:45.634 --> 14:49.305
The thing is, he's half
fairy, half troll.

14:49.388 --> 14:50.222
{\an1}Come on!

14:50.306 --> 14:52.141
{\an1}I let that dude sleep in
my laundry basket!

14:52.224 --> 14:53.142
Hey, fun bunch.

14:53.225 --> 14:55.769
Let's open the ears and
close the mouths, okay?

15:00.065 --> 15:02.693
{\an1}How did all this happen and
I didn't know about it?

15:02.776 --> 15:05.195
Do you know how many
secrets I've kept for you?

15:05.279 --> 15:06.363
That thing in
fifth grade--

15:06.447 --> 15:08.699
Everyone carried around an
extra pair of pants Morgan.

15:08.782 --> 15:09.491
It's not weird!

15:09.575 --> 15:10.326
I'm sorry, Dev.

15:10.409 --> 15:12.286
We didn't know if
you could handle it.

15:12.369 --> 15:14.204
{\an1}You didn't even give
me a chance.

15:15.039 --> 15:16.081
Last warning.

15:16.165 --> 15:19.168
Extra homework
or not?

15:19.251 --> 15:23.797
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

15:23.881 --> 15:24.506
<i>Peaseblossom: Objection!</i>

15:24.590 --> 15:25.507
<i>Overruled.</i>

15:25.591 --> 15:26.717
Badgering the witness!

15:26.800 --> 15:27.676
Sidebar.

15:27.760 --> 15:28.677
You're out of order!

15:28.761 --> 15:29.720
Thank you.

15:29.803 --> 15:31.388
The defense rests.

15:31.472 --> 15:33.724
You haven't argued
anything.

15:33.807 --> 15:35.768
Just said law things
for ten minutes.

15:35.851 --> 15:36.810
{\an3}Sustained!

15:36.894 --> 15:40.689
Now, Winston, you tried
to eat Reggie the bug.

15:40.773 --> 15:41.690
Technically speaking--

15:41.774 --> 15:43.734
Answer the question!

15:43.984 --> 15:46.987
I love Athenia, and
all its fairy folk.

15:47.071 --> 15:50.032
And so what if he mercilessly
tried to hack off a piece

15:50.115 --> 15:50.824
of the summerberry bush.

15:50.908 --> 15:53.035
At least he didn't
try and eat it.

15:53.118 --> 15:55.579
And a good thing too, because
that plants were sick.

15:55.663 --> 15:56.330
<i>That's right!</i>

15:56.413 --> 15:57.581
And I cleared
away the trash!

15:57.665 --> 15:59.083
And nursed it
back to life!

15:59.166 --> 15:59.792
{\an3}Lies!

15:59.875 --> 16:00.376
Have you no
shame, Other?

16:00.459 --> 16:01.168
When did this happen?

16:01.251 --> 16:03.212
Well, we tried to
tell Versitude,

16:03.295 --> 16:04.713
but she was all
"Run along!"

16:04.797 --> 16:05.631
and "Too busy!"

16:05.714 --> 16:08.008
{\an1}and "I have scary twig
things in my hair!"

16:08.092 --> 16:08.592
{\an1}Whatever.

16:08.676 --> 16:09.510
She's weird.

16:09.593 --> 16:10.177
<i>Is this true?</i>

16:10.260 --> 16:11.303
Why wasn't I told?

16:11.387 --> 16:15.557
These are the silly ramblings
of a common wood fairy.

16:15.641 --> 16:16.809
Silly?

16:16.892 --> 16:20.646
My ramblings are delightful
and charming, but never silly.

16:21.105 --> 16:22.773
Okay, well there was
that one time--

16:22.856 --> 16:24.316
I found this near
the vale.

16:24.400 --> 16:26.860
A whole briar of
summerberries is dying.

16:26.944 --> 16:28.195
It's his fault!

16:28.278 --> 16:30.114
Away with him!

16:31.657 --> 16:33.575
You can save the
summerberry bush?

16:33.659 --> 16:34.868
Yes, your majesty.

16:34.952 --> 16:35.869
Gladly.

16:35.953 --> 16:38.080
Without our protection
of the natural world,

16:38.163 --> 16:40.249
this planet would
cease to be.

16:40.332 --> 16:42.543
Go forth under the
protection of Athenia

16:42.626 --> 16:45.379
{\an1}and with our deepest
gratitude.

16:46.505 --> 16:47.214
Thank you!

16:47.297 --> 16:48.132
Thank you!

16:48.215 --> 16:49.717
We did it Winny!

16:49.800 --> 16:54.805
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

16:54.888 --> 16:58.642
{\an1}Your faith in Others could
signal the end of us.

16:58.726 --> 17:01.437
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

17:01.520 --> 17:03.647
Wisk.

17:03.731 --> 17:04.606
Measuring cup.

17:05.816 --> 17:06.692
Mop.

17:08.986 --> 17:10.112
One cup of vinegar.

17:16.242 --> 17:17.202
{\an1}Flour.

17:17.786 --> 17:18.537
I need flour!

17:18.619 --> 17:19.413
Where's the flour?!

17:19.496 --> 17:20.580
{\an3}Stay calm.

17:20.664 --> 17:23.916
{\an1}Remember: you own the cake,
the cake doesn't own you.

17:25.252 --> 17:27.588
Easy does it.

17:32.551 --> 17:35.429
Okay.

17:35.512 --> 17:37.890
Two cups of flour.

17:37.973 --> 17:38.474
Stop!

17:38.557 --> 17:39.683
Freeze!

17:39.767 --> 17:41.310
Don't move.

17:41.393 --> 17:42.811
Why are you
yelling at me?

17:42.895 --> 17:44.813
This is not good for
my Chi, Brendoni.

17:44.897 --> 17:47.357
That's baking
soda, not flour.

17:47.441 --> 17:50.194
We woiuld have had quite
a mess on our hands

17:50.277 --> 17:51.779
<i>if you'd poured</i>
<i>that in there.</i>

17:51.862 --> 17:53.030
Vinegar and
baking soda.

17:53.113 --> 17:53.781
Oof.

17:53.864 --> 17:54.823
Wait a second.

17:54.907 --> 17:57.201
I didn't make the mistake
last year, you did.

17:57.284 --> 17:59.161
Mistake?

17:59.244 --> 18:00.204
I never make mistakes!

18:00.287 --> 18:02.664
Last week you told us that
bread was a vegetable!

18:02.748 --> 18:04.500
Science will prove
me right!

18:04.792 --> 18:06.752
Principal Auntie Maddie wants
a Chocolate Vinegar cake?

18:06.835 --> 18:09.213
{\an1}I'll give her a Chocolate
Vinegar cake.

18:09.296 --> 18:10.297
I'll get the flour!

18:10.380 --> 18:13.175
{\an1}Frankly, Mr. McGillroy owes
Me a major apology.

18:13.258 --> 18:14.676
I could press charges.

18:14.760 --> 18:15.761
Seriously, Hailey?

18:15.844 --> 18:18.347
Okay, I hope your taste
buds are ready for a trip,

18:18.430 --> 18:20.432
because we're going
to flavor country.

18:20.516 --> 18:26.814
Behold, the greatest ever
Chocolate Vinegar Cake.

18:28.398 --> 18:28.732
What?!

18:28.816 --> 18:29.733
Where's my cake?

18:29.817 --> 18:31.276
Did you want some?

18:31.610 --> 18:33.195
Aunt Maddie, this
is unacceptable!

18:33.278 --> 18:35.155
This dog just ate
my homework!

18:35.239 --> 18:38.826
I'll take Mr. McGillroy's word
you completed your assignment.

18:40.285 --> 18:43.872
You are the most
annoying, odious,

18:43.956 --> 18:44.331
disgusting creature
I know.

18:44.414 --> 18:46.750
I work at it.

18:46.834 --> 18:47.960
Urgghhhhh.

18:50.629 --> 18:52.214
So, how was it?

18:52.297 --> 18:53.715
Incredible.

18:53.799 --> 18:54.925
Of course it was.

18:55.008 --> 18:56.468
It's what I do.

18:59.054 --> 19:00.430
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

19:00.514 --> 19:03.350
Here's the tricky thing
about the truth:

19:03.433 --> 19:05.352
You never know how an
Other is going to take it.

19:05.435 --> 19:08.188
There are things that
you don't understand.

19:08.272 --> 19:09.731
You're supposed to
be my bestfriend.

19:09.815 --> 19:12.734
In Athenia we don't lie because
it weighs us down,

19:12.818 --> 19:15.112
and makes it impossible
to fly light.

19:15.195 --> 19:17.531
I don't need a plane
ticket to fly home.

19:17.614 --> 19:19.324
What?

19:20.659 --> 19:21.451
I am fairy.

19:21.535 --> 19:24.872
But here Others get
hurt by the truth.

19:24.955 --> 19:25.873
You knew about this?

19:25.956 --> 19:26.790
{\an1}No!

19:26.874 --> 19:27.583
{\an1}Yes.

19:27.666 --> 19:29.376
But Devon, you
can't tell anyone.

19:29.459 --> 19:30.419
{\an3}Why not?

19:30.502 --> 19:34.548
And when an Other is hurt
anything can happen.

19:40.512 --> 19:42.890
There's leftover Chinese
food for dinner.

19:42.973 --> 19:45.726
We don't have to arm wrestle
over the last egg roll.

19:45.809 --> 19:47.728
You could have
it, see?

19:47.811 --> 19:48.478
Same old me.

19:48.562 --> 19:49.438
Just like this morning.

19:49.521 --> 19:52.524
Y'know, I think I'll
just call it a night.

19:54.359 --> 19:55.736
What?!

19:55.819 --> 20:00.324
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

20:00.407 --> 20:01.116
Mom!

20:01.199 --> 20:04.244
Oh, It's good to
see you, darling.

20:04.328 --> 20:05.245
{\an8}What are you
doing here?

20:05.329 --> 20:08.457
I know, we said we
wouldn't interfere, but--

20:08.540 --> 20:09.124
<i>It's alright.</i>

20:09.207 --> 20:11.793
{\an1}I'm one of those
cool moms.

20:12.044 --> 20:12.836
You're her--

20:12.920 --> 20:13.295
her--

20:13.378 --> 20:14.296
Her mother.

20:14.379 --> 20:17.466
The Queen of Athenia.

20:17.549 --> 20:19.593
{\an1}I wanted to thank
you in person.

20:19.676 --> 20:22.596
Our home was in great peril,
but now my people are safe.

20:22.679 --> 20:24.640
I don't want to
hear any of this.

20:24.723 --> 20:25.390
This isn't real.

20:25.474 --> 20:25.682
{\an1}It is.

20:25.766 --> 20:26.558
{\an1}Believe.

20:26.642 --> 20:28.268
{\an1}And you have been
kind to the princess.

20:28.352 --> 20:29.811
Princess??

20:29.895 --> 20:31.813
Yep, that's me.

20:31.897 --> 20:33.315
Fairy princess.

20:33.398 --> 20:36.193
Devon, you can't tell anyone
what you' ve seen and heard.

20:36.276 --> 20:38.320
The lives of thousands, and
of my daughter depend on it.

20:38.403 --> 20:40.530
<i>Peter: I'm home!</i>

20:41.406 --> 20:42.824
He'll see you!

20:42.908 --> 20:44.284
Keep Astral's secret.

20:44.368 --> 20:45.327
<i>Please.</i>

20:45.410 --> 20:46.954
It's to protect her.

20:49.456 --> 20:50.666
Please.

20:50.749 --> 20:51.875
{\an3}Hey.

20:51.959 --> 20:53.543
Dad, you're home.

20:53.627 --> 20:55.837
Yeah, it happens every
day at this time.

20:57.756 --> 20:58.674
You guys okay?

20:58.757 --> 21:03.679
Uh, yeah, just busting
through some geography.

21:03.762 --> 21:04.388
That Mr. Trainer.

21:04.471 --> 21:06.890
Yeah, he really
cracks the whip.

21:06.974 --> 21:08.725
Wi-cha!

21:08.809 --> 21:09.559
Are you guys hungry?

21:09.643 --> 21:11.812
Why don't I take
you out to Snug's?

21:11.895 --> 21:12.312
Uh, sure.

21:12.396 --> 21:14.564
That'd be great.

21:15.983 --> 21:20.696
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

21:20.779 --> 21:23.782
<i>Titania: Fairwell Peter.</i>

21:23.865 --> 21:30.706
{\an9}<i>♪</i>

21:41.008 --> 22:00.986
{\an9}<i>♪</i>
